@@eThe Roc Road: Western Corridor Governance Report@@N

@@yBureau of Western Routes, Patrol and Maintenance Division@@N
@@dFiled under: Joint Corridor, Kiess Relations, Crossroads Administration@@N

The Roc Road is Midgaard's western artery, and our half is
@@ymaintained to standard@@N. Every warden recites the @@WThree Civic
Oaths@@N at shift change. Every checkpoint conducts oath recitations
per the @@WOath of the Counted Step@@N. Gray-purple ash-mortar paving
from the @@dLantern Reforms@@N still bears weight because maintenance
clerks authorize resurfacing on a seven-year cycle, documented in
@@dpaving ledger, western drawer, volumes one through forty-six@@N.

Boundary sigils are repainted even when manpower prevents full
repairs, because the @@WOath of Stone@@N requires visible jurisdiction.
This is not vanity. This is @@ylegibility@@N. A road that cannot be
read cannot be governed. Our wardens understand this. Kiess does not.

@@yKiess's@@N western half operates through @@yconvoy compacts@@N -- shared
liability pools distributing losses across participants. A marshal
can delay departures, reroute through the Greenveil Spur, authorize
emergency payments to wayfolk. This is @@epragmatic@@N. Our Bureau
acknowledges its effectiveness. But it is @@rideologically concerning@@N.

Where Midgaard asks @@W"Who has lawful right to command?"@@N Kiess asks
@@y"What keeps goods and people alive tomorrow?"@@N Their founding
clause -- no sealed warrant from a predecessor shall bind a Kiess
citizen -- directly repudiates institutional continuity. Our
Continuity faction calls this civilizational negligence. Our
Reckoning faction notes Kiess repudiated those warrants because
@@rwe issued some of them@@N.

The central @@rCrossroads@@N is the governance challenge. Charter
boundaries blur. Violence spikes under unilateral control attempts.
The Joint Oversight Committee has not achieved quorum in four
consecutive sessions. Shared governance reduces bloodshed but
increases forms filed under @@d"disputed jurisdiction, pending."@@N

The @@dViolet Eclipse Cathedral@@N stands along the route; its ledgers
are classified @@drestricted review, tribunal authorization required@@N.

Four historical strata underlie the road: migration track, stone
route, military corridor, mercantile spine. Our Bureau maintains all
four layers. Kiess maintains whichever is currently profitable.

The Roc Road proves two incompatible philosophies can share a
corridor -- and that @@rsharing a corridor is not agreeing on its
purpose@@N. Our paving holds. Our oaths are spoken. Whether that is
enough depends on from which end of the road one asks.
